a. Ensure that payments for wages of JO personnel are supported with adequate documentation including duly approved accomplishment reports and DTRs.

The Municipal Treasurer explain the noted discrepancies in the cashbook and prepare adjusting entries to reflect the correct balance as of December 31, 2023; 

Henceforth, the Municipal Treasurer deposit her collections regularly and intact and discontinue the practice of retaining/withholding part of her collections pursuant to Section 69(4) of P. D. 1445 and Section 32 of the NGAS Manual for LGUs, Volume I, to ensure the safety and avoid risk of loss of government funds; and

The Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Accountant regularly reconcile their records to adjust/correct the difference in the Cash-Local Treasury account and errors could be rectified at the earliest possible time.

Enforce strictly the full settlement of all unliquidated cash advances as of December 31, 2023;

Prioritize issuance of demand letters to all accountable officers who are still in active service;

Impose the withholding of salary and the institution of other sanctions as provided under paragraphs 9.2 and 9.3 of COA Circular No. 97-002 dated February 10, 1997; and

Request for write-off the cash advances which have remained in active or non-moving in the books for 10 years or more and where settlement/collectivity could no longer be ascertained pursuant to COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016.

Prioritize the development of GAD PPAs that are realistic and attainable to ensure that direct, immediate and substantial benefits are provided to the public; 

Regularly monitor/review the GAD budget if it is being spent for what it was intended for and check on the actual cost of implementing the GAD activities to avoid over allocation;

Strengthen the monitoring and evaluation system to secure the effective and efficient implementation of GAD GPB; and

Consider attribution of the Municipality’s major programs to the GAD budget subject to HGDG assessment tool to maximize utilization of GAD Budget.

