Management includes in its Annual Budget, the budget of the Libacao College as part of its Economic Enterprise for review by the Office of the Sangguniang Panlalawigan;

Record all transactions related to the operation of the College in the General Fund as Economic Enterprise;

Close the Other Payable Account- Libacao College Special Trust Fund (LCST)in the Trust Fund books and transfer the balance of the account to the General Fund; and

The Municipal Accountant prepares and submits the financial statements of the economic enterprise for review and verification on the operation of the College in compliance with Section 313, Article II of R.A. 7160 and Section 159 of the Government Accounting Manual for LGUs.

We recommended that Management:
a. require the OIC-Municipal Engineer to provide a complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects pursuant to Item V of COA Circular No. 2015-008;
b. direct the Municipal Assessor to assist the OIC-Municipal Engineer in the assessment of the fair market value of the road lot component of all existing local roads under the deed of sale being sold or donated to the Municipality;
c. direct the Municipal GSO to prepare and maintain an LRIRRM and conduct required reconciliation with the Municipal Accountant between the list of inventory per LRIRRM with those recorded in the RPI; and
d. instruct the Municipal Accountant to (i) record completed infrastructure projects acquired thru fund transfers in the GF books and provide appropriate depreciation relative thereto; and (ii) take up the necessary correcting/adjusting entries to recognize completed projects from previous years and rectify erroneous provision of residual values in depreciating Road Networks account.

We recommended that Management:
a. require the OIC-LDRRM Officer to (i) monitor and evaluate the utilization of the LDRRMF based on the PPAs listed in the LDRRMFIP to ensure the full implementation of planned activities; (ii) prepare the Report on the Utilization of LDRRMF to be certified correct by the Municipal Accountant and submit the same to the Audit Team on or before the 15th day after the end of each month; and (iii) apply for fidelity bond as the AO for government-owned DRRM properties;
b. instruct the BAC Secretariat to (i) create/register an account with the GPPB Online Portal and upload/post thereto the necessary documentary requirements such as APPs, NOAs, and POs for Emergency Procurement under RA No. 11469 or the Bayanihan Act; (ii) comply strictly with the posting requirements provided under Section 9.0 of GPPB Circular No. 01-2020; and (iii) provide a satisfactory explanation as to their non-compliance with the posting requirements for Emergency Procurement under GPPB Circular No. 01-2020;
c. direct the Municipal Accountant in coordination with the MSWDO, the MHO, and the Barangay Councils to (i) submit to the Audit Team the distribution sheets of fisherfolks duly signed by the latter and the lists of families of possible active COVID-19 patients duly noted by the MHO for further evaluation of the transactions; and (ii) ensure that all supporting documents are provided with complete information;
d. comply strictly with the provisions of EO No. 51 whereby the NFA shall be the supplier of rice that the government entity would need in connection with its functions, unless a waiver is issued by the latter;
e. forge an appropriate MOA with the NFA to facilitate rice procurement arrangement; and
f. make a representation from the SB for the authority to open and maintain a separate bank account with an Authorized Government Depository Bank (AGDB) to secure the STF from commingling with the regular Trust Fund.

We recommended that Management:
a. require the BAC and its TWG to (i) observe caution in the possible errors in computation of NFCC submitted by the prospective bidders; (ii) carefully evaluate future bids whose key personnel and equipment were already pledged/used in other on-going projects; and (iii) require the contractors to submit DOLE-specific CSHP for each project to ensure the latter’s compliance with Occupational Safety and Health Standards set by the DOLE;
b. direct the OIC-Municipal Engineer to monitor the simultaneous implementation of construction projects by the same contractor to guard against possible delays or substandard quality of work;
c. advise the BAC and the OIC-Municipal Engineer to ensure strict compliance with DPWH Department Order No. 216 on the submission of copies of diaries or logbooks and photographic records with imprinted dates to facilitate the individual verification of the actual dates of the work progress for each project; and
d. instruct the Municipal Accountant to ensure that all supporting documents are complete and attached to the DVs before effecting payments.

